{"meta":{"title":"Moroni 3","canonicalUrl":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/3?lang=eng","contentType":"text/html","audio":[{"mediaUrl":"https://media2.ldscdn.org/assets/scriptures/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ/2015-11-2320-moroni-03-female-voice-64k-eng.mp3","voice":{"name":"female"}},{"mediaUrl":"https://media2.ldscdn.org/assets/scriptures/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ/2015-11-2320-moroni-03-male-voice-64k-eng.mp3","voice":{"name":"male"}}],"pageAttributes":{"data-asset-id":"d8eea313723aec5fb2100222f4e6778642ead1e4","data-aid":"128358135","data-aid-version":"5","data-content-type":"chapter","data-uri":"/scriptures/bofm/moro/3","lang":"eng","data-orig-id":"d8eea313723aec5fb2100222f4e6778642ead1e4","xmlns:xsi":"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"}},"content":{"head":{"page-meta-social":{"pageMeta":{"title":"Moroni 3","description":"Elders ordain priests and teachers by the laying on of hands. About A.D. 401–21."},"pageSocial":{"title":"Moroni 3","description":"Elders ordain priests and teachers by the laying on of hands. About A.D. 401–21."}},"links":[{"type":"array","rel":"stylesheet","orig-type":"text/css","href":"css/style_classic-scripture.css"}],"scripts":[]},"body":"<header>\n<p class=\"title-number\" data-aid=\"128358136\" id=\"title_number1\">Chapter 3</p>\n<p class=\"study-summary\" data-aid=\"128358137\" id=\"study_summary1\">Elders ordain priests and teachers by the laying on of hands. About <small>A.D.</small> 401–21.</p>\n</header>\n<div class=\"body-block\">\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358138\" id=\"p1\"><span class=\"verse-number\">1 </span>The manner which the disciples, who were called the <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note1a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>elders</a> of the church, <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note1b\"><sup class=\"marker\">b</sup>ordained</a> <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note1c\"><sup class=\"marker\">c</sup>priests</a> and teachers—</p>\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358139\" id=\"p2\"><span class=\"verse-number\">2 </span>After they had prayed unto the Father in the name of Christ, they <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note2a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>laid</a> their hands upon them, and said:</p>\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358140\" id=\"p3\"><span class=\"verse-number\">3 </span>In the name of Jesus Christ I ordain you to be a priest (or if he be a <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note3a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>teacher</a>, I ordain you to be a teacher) to preach repentance and <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note3b\"><sup class=\"marker\">b</sup>remission</a> of sins through Jesus Christ, by the endurance of faith on his name to the end. Amen.</p>\n<p class=\"verse\" data-aid=\"128358141\" id=\"p4\"><span class=\"verse-number\">4 </span>And after this manner did they <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note4a\"><sup class=\"marker\">a</sup>ordain</a> priests and teachers, according to the <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note4b\"><sup class=\"marker\">b</sup>gifts</a> and callings of God unto men; and they ordained them by the <a class=\"study-note-ref\" href=\"#note4c\"><sup class=\"marker\">c</sup>power</a> of the Holy Ghost, which was in them.</p>\n</div>\n<footer class=\"study-notes\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"chapter\">\n<li data-marker=\"3\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"verse\">\n<li data-marker=\"1\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note1a\" data-full-marker=\"1a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358142\" id=\"note1a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/6.1?lang=eng#p1\">Alma 6:1</a>. </span><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/elder?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Elder</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"b\" id=\"note1b\" data-full-marker=\"1b\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358143\" id=\"note1b_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/church-organization?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Church Organization</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"c\" id=\"note1c\" data-full-marker=\"1c\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358144\" id=\"note1c_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/6.3?lang=eng#p3\">Mosiah 6:3</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"2\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note2a\" data-full-marker=\"2a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358145\" id=\"note2a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/hands-laying-on-of?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Hands, Laying on of</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"3\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note3a\" data-full-marker=\"3a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358146\" id=\"note3a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/teacher?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Teacher</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"b\" id=\"note3b\" data-full-marker=\"3b\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358147\" id=\"note3b_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/remission-of-sins?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Remission of Sins</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"4\">\n<ul class=\"marker\" data-type=\"marker\">\n<li data-marker=\"a\" id=\"note4a\" data-full-marker=\"4a\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358148\" id=\"note4a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.32?lang=eng#p32\">D&amp;C 18:32</a>; <a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.39,60?lang=eng#p39\">20:39 (39, 60)</a>. </span><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/priesthood?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Priesthood</a>; <a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/priesthood-history-of?lang=eng\">Priesthood, History of</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"b\" id=\"note4b\" data-full-marker=\"4b\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358149\" id=\"note4b_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/god-gifts-of?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> God, Gifts of</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li data-marker=\"c\" id=\"note4c\" data-full-marker=\"4c\">\n<p data-aid=\"128358150\" id=\"note4c_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/13.37?lang=eng#p37\">1 Ne. 13:37</a>; <a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/moro/6.9?lang=eng#p9\">Moro. 6:9</a>.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</footer>","footnotes":{"note1a":{"id":"note1a","marker":"1a","pid":"128358138","context":"elders","text":"<p data-aid=\"128358142\" id=\"note1a_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"cross-ref\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/6.1?lang=eng#p1\">Alma 6:1</a>. </span><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/elder?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Elder</a>.</span></p>","referenceUris":[{"type":"scripture-ref","href":"/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/6.1?lang=eng#p1","text":"Alma 6:1"},{"type":"scripture-ref","href":"/study/scriptures/tg/elder?lang=eng","text":"TG Elder"}]},"note1b":{"id":"note1b","marker":"1b","pid":"128358138","context":"ordained","text":"<p data-aid=\"128358143\" id=\"note1b_p1\"><span data-note-category=\"tg\"><a class=\"scripture-ref\" href=\"/study/scriptures/tg/church-organization?lang=eng\"><small>TG</small> Church Organization</a>.</span></p>","referenceUris":[{"type":"scripture-ref","href":"/study/scriptures/tg/church-organization?lang=eng","text":"TG Church Organization"}]},"note1c":{"id":"note1c","marker":"1c","pid":"128358138","context":"priests","text":"<p data-aid=\"128358144\" id=\"note1c_p1\"><